cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular tree grammars and tree automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses storage and manipulation of trees. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper introduces a new weighted MSO-logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as the paper deals with weighted tree languages, which can be used in natural language processing and other AI applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also possible as the paper discusses the generation of tree languages, which can be used in programming language design and implementation.
